## 5. WebSocket Integration

### 5.1 Connection Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant FE as React App
    participant NS as Notification Service :8086

    FE->>NS: new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8086/ws/notify')
    NS-->>FE: Connection established
    loop On Kafka events
        NS->>FE: "ORDER_CREATED: {json}"
        NS->>FE: "DRIVER_ASSIGNED: {json}"
        NS->>FE: "ORDER_PICKED_UP: {json}"
        NS->>FE: "ORDER_DELIVERED: {json}"
    end
    FE->>FE: Parse event type + data
    FE->>FE: Update Zustand store + show toast
```

### 5.2 `useWebSocket` Hook Design

```javascript
// Conceptual вЂ” src/hooks/useWebSocket.js
function useWebSocket() {
  useEffect(() => {
    const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8086/ws/notify');
    ws.onmessage = (event) => {
      const [type, ...dataParts] = event.data.split(': ');
      const data = dataParts.join(': ');
      // Dispatch to stores based on type:
      // ORDER_CREATED    в†’ orderStore.addOrder(JSON.parse(data))
      // DRIVER_ASSIGNED  в†’ orderStore.updateOrder(...)
      // ORDER_PICKED_UP  в†’ orderStore.updateStatus(...)
      // ORDER_DELIVERED   в†’ orderStore.updateStatus(...)
      // Show toast notification
    };
    ws.onclose = () => { /* Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff */ };
    return () => ws.close();
  }, []);
}
```

