## 10. Routing & Guards

```javascript
// Route structure
<Routes>
  {/* Public */}
  <Route element={<AuthLayout />}>
    <Route path="/login" element={<LoginPage />} />
    <Route path="/register" element={<RegisterPage />} />
  </Route>

  {/* Customer routes вЂ” role: CUSTOMER */}
  <Route element={<ProtectedRoute allowedRoles={['CUSTOMER']} />}>
    <Route element={<AppLayout />}>
      <Route path="/" element={<CustomerDashboard />} />
      <Route path="/order/new" element={<PlaceOrderPage />} />
      <Route path="/orders" element={<MyOrdersPage />} />
      <Route path="/track/:orderId" element={<TrackOrderPage />} />
    </Route>
  </Route>

  {/* Driver routes вЂ” role: DRIVER */}
  <Route element={<ProtectedRoute allowedRoles={['DRIVER']} />}>
    <Route element={<AppLayout />}>
      <Route path="/driver" element={<DriverDashboard />} />
      <Route path="/driver/delivery/:orderId" element={<ActiveDeliveryPage />} />
      <Route path="/driver/orders" element={<DriverOrdersPage />} />
    </Route>
  </Route>

  <Route path="*" element={<NotFoundPage />} />
</Routes>
```

### ProtectedRoute Logic
1. Check `authStore.isAuthenticated`
2. If not в†’ redirect to `/login`
3. If yes в†’ check `authStore.role` against `allowedRoles`
4. If role mismatch в†’ redirect to appropriate dashboard
5. If OK в†’ render `<Outlet />`

